<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-6510] Don&apos;t drop local mutations without a hint</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6510</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SP.insertLocal() uses a regular DroppableRunnable, thus timed out local mutations get dropped without leaving a hint. SP.insertLocal() should be using LocalMutationRunnable instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note: hints are the context here, not consistency.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12685590">CASSANDRA-6510</key>
